A session is set even if the user is not authenticated.
While a user is logged in, `passport` put some data in the current session.
When the user go out, `passport` cleans those data, but let the session.

But if needed, you can manually destroy the current session:
- Add option `unset: 'destroy'` in [your session middleware constructor](https://github.com/SnowdreamCMS/nodejs-gulp-template/blob/master/app.js#L49)
- Update your logout code:

``` js
app.get('/logout', function(req, res) {
    req.logout();
    req.session = null;
    res.redirect('/');
});
```

